ts penalised.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"What is scaled content abuse in SEO?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Google defines scaled content abuse as generating many pages primarily to manipulate rankings rather than help users — typically involving large amounts of unoriginal content regardless of how it's produced. It's treated as a spam policy violation and can result in a site-wide ranking penalty.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"How do I get my content into Google AI Overviews?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"There's no direct opt-in. Google's guidance says to follow core SEO best practices, keep content accessible, and make it genuinely useful. Practically: lead sections with direct answers, use clear structure and headings, include definitions and summaries, and ensure your pages are indexed and crawlable. High organic rankings correlate strongly with AI Overview inclusion.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"How do I show up in ChatGPT and Perplexity search results?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Both tools pull from indexed web content and use authority signals similar to traditional SEO. Strong structured content, clear entity signals, high-quality external links, and direct answers that are easy to extract all help. Building a consistent topical presence around your area of expertise is more effective than optimising individual pages.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Do backlinks still matter in AI SEO?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Yes — but 